Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Seidler, Michael J., 1985, &ldquo;Freedom and Moral Therapy in
Leibniz,&rdquo; <em>Studia Leibnitiana</em>, 17 (1): 15&ndash;35.</li>

<li>Strickland, Lloyd, 2006a, &ldquo;Leibniz on Whether the World
Increases in Perfection,&rdquo; <em>British Journal for the History of
Philosophy</em>, 14 (1): 51&ndash;68.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006b, <em>Leibniz Reinterpreted</em>,
London: Continuum.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Leibniz on Eternal
Punishment,&rdquo; <em>British Journal for the History of
Philosophy</em>, 17 (2): 307&ndash;331.</li>

<li>Youpa, Andrew, 2005, &ldquo;Rationalist Moral Philosophy,&rdquo;
in <em>A Companion to Rationalism</em>, Alan Nelson (ed.), Oxford:
Blackwell Publishing.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

